Description:
A multi-supplier, multi-Lot Framework for the acquisition of Planned, Repairs, Maintenance and Specialist Services Contractors available to Members of NE Procurement and other Contracting Bodies within the North East of England.

The Framework is in three sections

Section 1: Planned  Maintenance Work (10 Lots – Regional)
This section covers maintenance work that is planned and budgeted by the Contracting Body as part of their programme of works. 
Lot 1.1 Plumbing; 
Lot 1.2 Heating; 
Lot 1.3 Electrical;
Lot 1.4 Roofing; 
Lot 1.5 Paint & Decorating; 
Lot 1.6 Windows & Doors; 
Lot 1.7 Carpentry & Joinery; 
Lot 1.8 Plastering; 
Lot 1.9 General Building;
Lot 1.10 Complete Service Provision

Section 2: Responsive Repairs and Maintenance (9 Lots – each sub-divided into 4 sub-regional areas )
This section cover covers reactive and responsive repair work and ad hoc work that cannot be planned and scheduled
Lot 2.1 Plumbing; 
Lot 2.2 Heating; 
Lot 2.3 Electrical; 
Lot 2.4 Roofing; 
Lot 2.5 Paint & Decorating; 
Lot 2.6 Joinery (including Windows & Doors); 
Lot 2.7 Rendering & Plaster Work; 
Lot 2.8 General Building; 
Lot 2.9 Complete Service Provision

Section 3: Specialist Services (8 Lots – each sub-divided into 4 sub-regional areas)
This section covers work of a specialist nature that could be both Planned and Responsive maintenance.
Lot 3.1 Scaffolding; 
Lot 3.2 Flooring; 
Lot 3.3 Tiling (Floor & Wall); 
Lot 3.4 Rendering & External Wall Insulation; 
Lot 3.5 Cavity Wall Insulation; 
Lot 3.6 Adaptations (DDA); 
Lot 3.7 Glazing; 
Lot 3.8 Fencing
